# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Vercel Web Analytics (`@vercel/analytics`) is **already installed and properly configured** in this project. No changes were necessary.

## Verification Steps Completed

### 1. Fetched Latest Documentation
- Retrieved the official Vercel Analytics quickstart guide from: https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Confirmed the latest installation instructions for React/Vite projects

### 2. Verified Existing Configuration
The project already has the correct setup according to the latest Vercel documentation:

**Package Installation:**
- ✅ `@vercel/analytics@^2.0.1` is present in package.json dependencies

**Component Integration:**
- ✅ Correct import statement in `src/App.jsx`:
  ```jsx
  import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";
  ```
- ✅ Component properly placed in the App component:
  ```jsx
  <Analytics />
  ```
- ✅ Component is positioned at the end of the main div, following best practices

### 3. Build Verification
- ✅ Dependencies installed successfully with `npm install`
- ✅ Build completed successfully with `npm run build`
- ✅ No new errors introduced (existing linting issues are unrelated to Analytics)

## Framework Detection
- **Framework:** React 19.2.4 with Vite 7.3.1
- **Package Manager:** npm (package-lock.json present)
- **Build Tool:** Vite

## Configuration Details
The Analytics component is integrated in the root App component (`src/App.jsx`), which is the recommended approach for React applications. The component will automatically:
- Track page views
- Collect visitor analytics data when deployed to Vercel
- Require no additional configuration

## Next Steps
Once this application is deployed to Vercel:
1. Analytics will automatically begin collecting data
2. Verify proper setup by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/<unique-path>/view`
3. View analytics data in the Vercel dashboard

